M|Mode|tx|Use the least powerful md that can handle each role to conserve cost and increase speed.
M|Mode|**Me|use a fast, cheap md. Most implementation tasks are mechanical when the plan is well-specified.
M|Mode|**In|use a standard md.
M|Mode|**Ar|use the most capable available md.
M|Mode|**Ta|**
M|Mode|it|Touches 1-2 files w/ a complete spec → cheap md
M|Mode|it|Touches multiple files w/ integration concerns → standard md
M|Mode|it|Requires ds judgment or broad codebase understanding → most capable md
M|Hand|Impl|
M|Hand|**DO|** Proceed to spec compliance rv.
M|Hand|**DO|** The implementer done the work but flagged doubts. Read the concerns before proceeding. If the concerns are abt correctness or scope, address them before rv. If they're observations (e.g., "this file is getting large"), note them and proceed to rv.
M|Hand|**NE|** The implementer needs information that wasn't provided. Provide the missing context and re-dispatch.
M|Hand|blk|** The implementer cannot complete the task. Assess the blocker:
M|Hand|tx|1. If it's a context problem, provide more context and re-dispatch w/ the same md
M|Hand|tx|2. If the task requires more reasoning, re-dispatch w/ a more capable md
M|Hand|tx|3. If the task is too large, break it into smaller pieces
M|Hand|tx|4. If the plan itself is wrong, escalate to the human
M|Hand|tx|**Never** ignore an escalation or force the same md to retry w/o changes. If the implementer said it's stuck, something needs to change.
M|Prom|it|`./implementer-pm.md` - Dispatch implementer subagent
M|Prom|it|`./spec-reviewer-pm.md` - Dispatch spec compliance reviewer subagent
M|Prom|it|`./code-qual-reviewer-pm.md` - Dispatch code qual reviewer subagent
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Exam|You|I'm using Subagent-Driven dv to execute this plan.
M|Exam|[Rea|doc/superpowers/plans/feature-plan.md]
M|Exam|tx|[Extract all 5 tasks w/ full text and context]
M|Exam|tx|[cr TodoWrite w/ all tasks]
M|Exam|Task|Hook installation script
M|Exam|tx|[Get Task 1 text and context (already extracted)]
M|Exam|tx|[Dispatch implementation subagent w/ full task text + context]
M|Exam|Impl|"Before I begin - shd the hook be installed at us or sy level?"
M|Exam|You|"us level (~/.config/superpowers/hooks/)"
M|Exam|Impl|"Got it. Implementing now..."
M|Exam|[Lat|
M|Exam|it|Implemented install-hook command
M|Exam|it|Added tests, 5/5 passing
M|Exam|- Se|Found I missed --force flag, added it
M|Exam|it|Committed
M|Exam|tx|[Dispatch spec compliance reviewer]
M|Exam|Spec|✅ Spec compliant - all requirements met, nothing extra
M|Exam|tx|[Get git SHAs, dispatch code qual reviewer]
M|Exam|Code|Strengths: Good tst coverage, clean. Issues: None. Approved.
M|Exam|tx|[Mark Task 1 complete]
M|Exam|Task|Recovery modes
M|Exam|tx|[Get Task 2 text and context (already extracted)]
M|Exam|tx|[Dispatch implementation subagent w/ full task text + context]
M|Exam|Impl|[No questions, proceeds]
M|Exam|Impl|
M|Exam|it|Added verify/repair modes
M|Exam|it|8/8 tests passing
M|Exam|- Se|All good
M|Exam|it|Committed
M|Exam|tx|[Dispatch spec compliance reviewer]
M|Exam|Spec|❌ Issues:
M|Exam|- Mi|Progress reporting (spec says "rp every 100 items")
M|Exam|- Ex|Added --json flag (not requested)
M|Exam|tx|[Implementer fixes issues]
M|Exam|Impl|Removed --json flag, added progress reporting
M|Exam|tx|[Spec reviewer reviews again]
M|Exam|Spec|✅ Spec compliant now
M|Exam|tx|[Dispatch code qual reviewer]
M|Exam|Code|Strengths: Solid. Issues (Important): Magic number (100)
M|Exam|tx|[Implementer fixes]
M|Exam|Impl|Extracted PROGRESS_INTERVAL constant
M|Exam|tx|[Code reviewer reviews again]
M|Exam|Code|✅ Approved
M|Exam|tx|[Mark Task 2 complete]
M|Exam|tx|...
M|Exam|tx|[After all tasks]
M|Exam|tx|[Dispatch final code-reviewer]
M|Exam|Fina|All requirements met, ready to merge
M|Exam|tx|Done!
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Adva|**vs|**
M|Adva|it|Subagents follow TDD naturally
M|Adva|it|Fresh context per task (no confusion)
M|Adva|it|Parallel-safe (subagents don't interfere)
M|Adva|it|Subagent can ask questions (before AND during work)
M|Adva|**vs|**
M|Adva|it|Same sn (no handoff)
M|Adva|it|Continuous progress (no waiting)
M|Adva|it|rv checkpoints automatic
M|Adva|**Ef|**
M|Adva|it|No file reading overhead (controller provides full text)
M|Adva|it|Controller curates exactly what context is needed
M|Adva|it|Subagent gets complete information upfront
M|Adva|it|Questions surfaced before work begins (not after)
M|Adva|**Qu|**
M|Adva|it|Self-rv catches issues before handoff
M|Adva|- Tw|spec compliance, then code qual
M|Adva|it|rv loops ensure fixes actually work
M|Adva|it|Spec compliance prevents over/under-building
M|Adva|it|Code qual ensures implementation is well-built
M|Adva|**Co|**
M|Adva|it|More subagent invocations (implementer + 2 reviewers per task)
M|Adva|it|Controller does more prep work (extracting all tasks upfront)
M|Adva|it|rv loops add iterations
M|Adva|it|But catches issues early (cheaper than debugging later)
M|Red |**Ne|**
M|Red |it|Start implementation on main/master branch w/o explicit us consent
M|Red |it|Skip reviews (spec compliance OR code qual)
M|Red |it|Proceed w/ unfixed issues
M|Red |it|Dispatch multiple implementation subagents in parallel (conflicts)
M|Red |it|Make subagent read plan file (provide full text instead)
M|Red |it|Skip scene-setting context (subagent needs to understand where task fits)
M|Red |it|Ignore subagent questions (answer before letting them proceed)
M|Red |it|Accept "close enough" on spec compliance (spec reviewer found issues = not done)
M|Red |it|Skip rv loops (reviewer found issues = implementer fixes = rv again)
M|Red |it|Let implementer self-rv replace actual rv (both are needed)
M|Red |it|**Start code qual rv before spec compliance is ✅** (wrong order)
M|Red |it|Move to nx task while either rv has open issues
M|Red |**If|**
M|Red |it|Answer clearly and completely
M|Red |it|Provide additional context if needed
M|Red |it|Don't rush them into implementation
M|Red |**If|**
M|Red |it|Implementer (same subagent) fixes them
M|Red |it|Reviewer reviews again
M|Red |it|Repeat until approved
M|Red |it|Don't skip the re-rv
M|Red |**If|**
M|Red |it|Dispatch fix subagent w/ specific instructions
M|Red |it|Don't try to fix manually (context pollution)
M|Inte|**Re|**
M|Inte|- **|using-git-worktrees** - REQUIRED: Set up isolated workspace before starting
M|Inte|- **|writing-plans** - Creates the plan this skill executes
M|Inte|- **|requesting-code-rv** - Code rv template for reviewer subagents
M|Inte|- **|finishing-a-dv-branch** - Complete dv after all tasks
M|Inte|**Su|**
M|Inte|- **|tst-driven-dv** - Subagents follow TDD for each task
M|Inte|**Al|**
M|Inte|- **|executing-plans** - Use for parallel sn instead of same-sn execution